# EasyProxi Upgrade Notes

## Overview
Upgraded EasyProxi from a simple landing page with proxy form to a full multi-service web platform with browser UI, proxy system, download page, clean routing, and scalable backend structure.

## Domain Structure
- easyproxi.online → Main landing page (index.html)
- browser.easyproxi.online → Frontend browser UI (browser.html)
- proxy.easyproxi.online → Proxy backend (/api/proxy)
- server.easyproxi.online → API/backend services (/api/*)

## Frontend Changes

### Landing Page (index.html)
- Restored original landing page design
- Updated navigation links to use clean URLs (/download)
- Maintained dark neon design and overlay panel

### Browser UI (browser.html)
- New browser-like interface with toolbar
- URL input bar with search functionality
- Back/Forward/Reload buttons
- Iframe loads proxied content via /api/proxy
- Draggable overlay panel remains visible above iframe
- Responsive design for desktop/mobile

### URL Handling Improvements
- Enhanced normalizeUrl function
- Converts "google.com" to "https://google.com"
- Searches Google for terms without dots (e.g., "youtube")
- Supports full URLs

### Download Page (download.html)
- New page: "Download EasyProxi Browser"
- Platform buttons: Windows, Mac, Linux
- Simulates downloads (alerts for demo)
- Back to Home button

## Backend API (server.easyproxi.online)

### New Endpoints
- GET /api/status → Returns uptime and status
- POST /api/usage → Tracks data usage (requires API key)
- GET /api/user → Returns mock user data (requires API key)

### Proxy System
- Kept simple /api/proxy endpoint
- Fetches external pages and returns HTML
- Basic headers handling

## Routing (vercel.json)
- /download → /download.html
- /browser → /browser.html
- / → /index.html (landing)

## Desktop App (desktop_app.py)
- Python app using pywebview
- Loads https://browser.easyproxi.online
- Window: 1200x800, title "EasyProxi Browser"
- Build instructions for Windows (.exe), Mac (.app), Linux (binary)

## Code Quality
- Modular and clean code
- No duplicate logic
- Added comments where helpful
- Maintained existing dark neon design
- Responsive across devices

## Files Modified/Created
- Updated: index.html, script.js, style.css
- Created: browser.html, download.html, vercel.json, api/status.js, api/usage.js, api/user.js, desktop_app.py

## Architecture
- Scalable structure with separate concerns
- Clean URL routing without .html extensions
- API key support for backend services
- Desktop app for native experience